Work_Description:
On behalf of the project team at both Develop Nova Scotia and Civic 34 Hazelhurst, Strum Consulting is making an application for a New Service Application (NSA) for Civic 2 Maitland Street, PID 00097568.  The intent of the application is to move the location of the existing 3.05m wide service easement (and water lateral) that cross Civic 34 so that a dwelling can be developed on Civic 34 parcel.  The building permit application for the dwelling will follow separately.

Based on discussions with DNS & the project team at Civic 34 Hazelhurst, we understand the existing sprinkler system within the warehouse facility at 2 Maitland St is not currently functional, but the domestic water system is active.  We understand the existing warehouse facility is slated for redevelopment in the medium term but at this time development concepts have not yet been finalized.  Construction of the dwelling at Civic 34 Hazelhurst is intended to start in 2022.

In reviewing Halifax Water's existing infrastructure in the area surrounding Civic 2 Maitland Street, Maitland Street does not currently contain water service, Newcastle Street contains a 150mm diameter service, and Hazehurst Street contains a 200mm diameter service that crosses a private utility easement (at Civic 34) in order to provide service to the lot.  In order to maintain flexibility for future planning and development in the area, and avoid future disruptions on Civic 34 Hazelhurst following construction, a replacement 200mm diameter water supply line is proposed to be installed within a new service easement and capped at the property line (refer to Servicing Drawings).  A 25mm domestic lateral will be connected to the new 200mm water supply line and connected to the existing warehouse in order to maintain domestic service.  

Upon demolition of the existing warehouse facility, the 25mm domestic water lateral will be disconnected from the 200mm lateral and abandoned and any future development will connect to the newly installed and capped 200mm water supply lateral.

Please find attached to this application the following documents:
1) NSA1- New Service & Renewal Application Form;
2) Drawings 18-6401 - C01 Rev0  & 18-6401 - C02 Rev0 (Plan & Profile drawings for servicing of both Civic 34 Hazelhurst & moving water service easement for Civic 2 Maitland St);
3) Correspondence from Dan Goodspeed (Project Architect) discussing warehouse use & building code classifications for storage buildings of similar size & configuration as the existing warehouse building at Civic 2 Maitland Street;
